<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="451" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,536,1030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,536,562]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kamiya" authorityName="Kamiya" authorityYear="1965" box="[561,814,536,562]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis box="[561,719,536,562]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">A. nigripennis</emphasis>
Kamiya
</taxonomicName>
in colour pattern but can be separated from the latter by slightly rounded body shape (
<figureCitation box="[485,581,572,598]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Fig. 13a</figureCitation>
), the triangular penis guide in inner view (
<figureCitation box="[1061,1157,572,598]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1114,1157,572,598]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" unit="g" value="13.0">13g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) and ventrite 1 with fine punctures at middle (
<figureCitation box="[391,489,608,635]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Fig. 13d</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamiya" authorityYear="1965" box="[542,702,608,634]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis box="[542,702,608,634]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">A. nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it has an elongate oval body shape (
<figureCitation box="[1124,1221,608,634]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1348,1372]" captionTargetBox="[173,1417,395,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-116@19.[151,1436,381,1324]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Axinoscymnus nigripennis Kamiya, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651193" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651193/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Fig. 12a</figureCitation>
), the parallel sided penis guide in inner view (
<figureCitation box="[450,545,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1348,1372]" captionTargetBox="[173,1417,395,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-116@19.[151,1436,381,1324]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Axinoscymnus nigripennis Kamiya, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651193" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651193/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[502,545,644,670]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" unit="g" value="12.0">12g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) and ventrite 1 with coarse punctures at middle (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1191,644,671]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1348,1372]" captionTargetBox="[173,1417,395,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-116@19.[151,1436,381,1324]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Axinoscymnus nigripennis Kamiya, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651193" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651193/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Fig. 12d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="452" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,536,1030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,680,706]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[399,563,680,707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.54" metricValueMax="1.66" metricValueMin="1.42" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" unit="mm" value="1.54" valueMax="1.66" valueMin="1.42">1.42–1.66 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[630,794,680,707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.175" metricValueMax="1.29" metricValueMin="1.06" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" unit="mm" value="1.175" valueMax="1.29" valueMin="1.06">1.06–1.29 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[856,1020,680,707]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" metricValueMax="9.1" metricValueMin="7.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" unit="mm" value="0.82" valueMax="0.91" valueMin="0.73">0.73–0.91 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.28–1.34, EL/EW: 1–1.03, PL/PW: 0.47–0.49, HW/PW: 0.66–0.70, PW/EW: 0.66–0.67.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,536,1030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">
Body slightly oval, moderately convex, dorsum with white pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[991,1117,752,778]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Figs 13a–c</figureCitation>
). Head, antennae and mouthparts yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[414,498,788,814]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Figs 1a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[510,553,788,814]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">13c</figureCitation>
), tip of mandibles dark brown. Pronotum and scutellar shield yellowish brown. Elytra black with narrowly apical margins yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[838,968,824,851]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Figs 13a–b</figureCitation>
). Prothoracic hypomeron and prosternum yellowish brown. Mesoventrite and elytral epipleurae blackish brown. Metaventrite black. Legs yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,536,1030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">
Head with fine frontal punctures, slightly larger than eye facets, 0.5–1.0 diameters apart. Eye densely faceted, interocular distance about 0.29 times of head width (
<figureCitation box="[742,827,932,958]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Figs 1a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[840,884,932,958]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">13c</figureCitation>
). Pronotal punctures slightly larger than those on frons, 0.5–1.5 diameters apart. Surface of elytra with punctures much larger than those on pronotum, separated by 1.0–2.0 diameters.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" startId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" targetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1976,2037]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1976,2000]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">FIGURE 13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Peng et Chen" authorityName="Peng et Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[294,731,1977,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pingxiangicus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[294,587,1977,2000]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus</emphasis>
Peng et Chen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[741,798,1977,2001]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[741,798,1977,2001]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[811,824,1977,2001]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">a</emphasis>
dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[954,968,1977,2001]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">b</emphasis>
lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1099,1110,1977,2001]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">c</emphasis>
frontal view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1246,1260,1977,2001]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">d</emphasis>
abdomen 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1365,1376,1977,2001]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">e</emphasis>
penis 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,159,2012,2036]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">f</emphasis>
tegmen, lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[378,391,2013,2037]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">g</emphasis>
tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[720,756,2013,2037]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">a–c</emphasis>
: 0.5 mm, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[860,874,2013,2037]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">d</emphasis>
: 0.1 mm, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[978,1015,2013,2037]" pageId="20" pageNumber="451">e–g</emphasis>
: 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="21" pageNumber="452">
Abdominal postcoxal lines complete and moderately recurved, reaching 2/3 length of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1273,1370,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="452">Fig. 13d</figureCitation>
), area enclosed by the lines finely and sparsely punctate, irregularly distributed, broadly smooth along the lines; ventrite 1 with fine and sparse punctures at middle, irregularly distributed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="21" pageNumber="452">
Male genitalia. Penis short and slender, slightly broadened at base, apex pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1209,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="452">Fig. 13e</figureCitation>
); tegmen with penis guide in lateral view widest at base, gradually tapering to apex (
<figureCitation box="[858,949,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="452">Fig. 13f</figureCitation>
), in inner view subtriangular and stout (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="452">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[151,196,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.3" pageId="21" pageNumber="452" unit="g" value="13.0">13g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), about 1/2 length of parameres; parameres stout and elongate oval with few setae at apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="452">Fig. 13f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
